#* {{quote-journal|en|url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/weekly-standard/the-rise-of-the-latte-town|title=The Rise of the Latte Town|date=1997-09-15|author=David Brooks|authorlink=David Brooks (commentator)|work=Washington Examiner|passage=In the 1970s, [Daniel] Bell saw '''antinomianism''' all around him, and his thesis struck a chord with many. Well, '''antinomianism''' never hit many places in America, like the evangelical Christian communities.}}
